main event: A bright, oval-shaped object was observed in the sky over Maracaibo, Venezuela on November 8, 1960.
interesting points: The object changed color from red to blue to green.
The object was estimated to be about 150 feet in diameter.
The object was observed to be hovering, accelerating, and decelerating.
The sighting was observed by several citizens and a professional photographer.
The report suggests the object was likely caused by some natural phenomenon.
witnesses: Several citizens and a professional photographer
photographs: No photographs present in the document
